subSubSection.paragraph:
Differential diagnosis. When compared to the other eriophyoid mite species found on plants in the family Proteaceae ,
A. argentae
is most similar to
A. proteae
[based on the original description and illustrations (
Meyer 1981
)] but differs by having: 7 -rayed empodia ( 6 -rayed in
A. proteae
); the absence of a dart-shaped mark at the posterior of the median line on the prodorsal shield (present in
A. proteae
); submedian lines on the prodorsal shield that converge toward the admedian lines (the first submedian line diverges onto the second submedian at about halfway on
A. proteae
); scapular setae that are about 21–25 µm long (about 55 µm long on
A. proteae
).
